Claims Claims: 1. An apparatus comprising: at least one processor; and at least one memory storing instructions that, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the apparatus at least to: receive an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by a user equipment; determine, based on the indication, a privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment based on the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; and apply the determined privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment. 2. The apparatus according to claim 1, wherein the stored instructions further cause, when executed by the at least one processor, the apparatus at least to: apply the determined privacy enhancing technique by applying the determined privacy enhancing technique on a machine learning model or on data collected from the user equipment; and after applying the determined privacy enhancing technique, share the machine learning model with the user equipment, or share the collected data with a network entity. 3. The apparatus according to claim 2, wherein the network entity is network data analytics function. 4. The apparatus according to claim 3, wherein the network data analytics function comprises a model training logical function. 5. The apparatus according to any of the preceding claims, wherein the privacy enhancing technique is a homomorphic encryption method. 6. The apparatus according to any of the preceding claims, wherein the stored instructions further cause, when executed by the at least one processor, the apparatus at least to: 

 determine the privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment by determining which one of multiple privacy enhancing techniques is supported by the user equipment. 7. The apparatus according to claim 6, wherein each of said multiple privacy enhancing techniques requires at least one requirement of a different level from the user equipment. 8. The apparatus according to claim 7, wherein the at least one requirement comprises at least one of a computation power requirement, a memory requirement or a capacity requirement. 9. The apparatus according to any of the preceding claims, wherein the apparatus is an application function or a network function, and the stored instructions further cause, when executed by the at least one processor, the apparatus at least to: transmit, to an access and mobility management function, a request to provide the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; and receive from the access and mobility management function, based on the request, the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment. 10. The apparatus according to any of claims 1 to 8, wherein the apparatus is a wireless network node, and the stored instructions further cause, when executed by the at least one processor, the apparatus at least to: receive the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment from an access and mobility function without requesting. 11. The apparatus according to any of claims 1 to 8, wherein the apparatus is another user equipment, and the stored instructions further cause, when executed by the at least one processor, the apparatus at least to: receive the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment from the user equipment or from a core network of the user equipment. 12. An apparatus comprising: at least one processor; and at least one memory storing instructions that, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the apparatus at least to: 

 receive, from a user equipment, an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; store the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to the at least one memory of the apparatus; and transmit the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to a unified data management function. 13. The apparatus according to claim 12, wherein the stored instructions further cause, when executed by the at least one processor, the apparatus at least to: transmit the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to a wireless network node without receiving a request. 14. The apparatus according to claim 12 or claim 13, wherein the stored instructions further cause, when executed by the at least one processor, the apparatus at least to: receive, from an application function or a network function, a request to provide the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; and transmit, based on the request, the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to the application function or the network function. 15. A method, comprising: receiving an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by a user equipment; determining, based on the indication, a privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment based on the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; and applying the determined privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment. 16. A method, comprising: receiving, from a user equipment, an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; storing the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to the at least one memory of the apparatus; and 

 transmitting the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to a unified data management function. 17. An apparatus comprising: means for receiving an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by a user equipment; means for determining, based on the indication, a privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment based on the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; and means for applying the determined privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment. 18. An apparatus comprising: means for receiving, from a user equipment, an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; means for storing the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to the at least one memory of the apparatus; and means for transmitting the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to a unified data management function. 19. A non-transitory computer readable medium comprising program instructions that, when executed by an apparatus, cause the apparatus to perform at least the following: receiving an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by a user equipment; determining, based on the indication, a privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment based on the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; and applying the determined privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment. 20. A non-transitory computer readable medium comprising program instructions that, when executed by an apparatus, cause the apparatus to perform at least the following: receiving, from a user equipment, an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; 

 storing the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to the at least one memory of the apparatus; and transmitting the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to a unified data management function. 21. A computer readable medium comprising program instructions that, when executed by an apparatus, cause the apparatus to perform at least the method of claim 15 or 16. 22. A computer program comprising instructions for causing an apparatus to perform at least the method of claim 15 or 16. 23. A system comprising: at least one processor and at least one memory storing instructions that, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the system at least to: receive an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by a user equipment; determine, based on the indication, a privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment based on the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; apply the determined privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; receive, from the user equipment, the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; store the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to the at least one memory of the apparatus; and transmit the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to a unified data management function. 24. A system comprising: means for receiving an indication of at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by a user equipment; means for determining, based on the indication, a privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment based on the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; 

means for applying the determined privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; means for receiving, from the user equipment, the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment; means for storing the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to the at least one memory of the apparatus; and means for transmitting the indication of the at least one privacy enhancing technique supported by the user equipment to a unified data management function.
